## User Review Required
> [!WARNING]
> Regarding `Kernel.run_single`: In my previous implementation, `Kernel.run(event_batch)` naturally generates the `state_chain`. If `ReplayEngine` iterates step-by-step to recompute the chain itself manually via `run_single`, should the Replay Engine itself house the mathematical hashing formulas (stripping hashing out of `Kernel` completely) or should `Kernel` still produce the structural `state_chain` which ReplayEngine simply inspects / matches per step? *(I recommend the Kernel STILL producing the hashes independently inside its `KernelResult`, effectively giving us dual computation proofs when ReplayEngine re-runs it and matches the chains natively!)*
